message: Growth serum is key for value, but use it strategically! Apply it twice to a single small or medium ingredient (like monkey, lizard, frog) or to a newly combined item (like a 'flying' creature). Do NOT use growth serum a third time on any item, it drastically reduces value. Also, be careful with large creatures like the elephant; their second growth serum application often leads to negative value. Mutation catalyst is always useless; avoid it entirely. Combining multiple *already grown* items also leads to significantly negative values. Your highest scores will likely come from combining 2-3 diverse basic ingredients (land, water, air) and then applying growth serum twice to that *newly formed* combined item.

message: Growth serum is your best friend, but use it wisely! Apply growth serum twice to small and medium ingredients to make 'super-grown' items, which will increase their value significantly (e.g., 10-15 points). For large ingredients, only use growth serum *once* to get a 'grown' item (around 15 points); using it a second time will turn them negative. The mutation catalyst is useless. To achieve high scores, combine 'super-grown' items that live in different environments (e.g., air + land, water + air) for scores around 25-30. Combining 'super-grown' items that cover all three environments (land, water, air) can yield up to 40 points. Be careful not to combine too many items or items with vastly different sizes, as this can lead to highly negative values.

message: The key to high scores is combining items with distinct 'lives in' features. Aim to combine items that 'live on land', 'live in the air', and 'live in the water' into a single item, as this consistently yields the highest values (around 20-35).
